timeline.bodyText:
The tree includes the new keyword. I feel we can be slightly more precise and report on the expression only.
I also wonder if we want to handle cases where we do not really own the exception, such as:
try { 
 doSomethingThrowingUsernameNotFoundException();
} catch (UsernameNotFoundException e) {
  if (/* whatever test */) {
    doSomething();
  } else {
   throw e; // would report here
  }

}

