timeline.bodyText:
I feel this condition is not enough, or will not report only on very trivial case. If I write something like the following, there is going to be 2 FPs:
 public static class MyUserDetailsService4 implements UserDetailsService {
    @Override
    public MyUserDetails loadUserByUsername(String s) throws UsernameNotFoundException {
      if (s.equals("yolo"))
        throw new UsernameNotFoundException(""); // Compliant

      switch(s) {
        case "admin":
          throw new UsernameNotFoundException(""); // Compliant
        case "batman":
          break;
      }
      return null;
    }
  }

In order to handle this case, I would use a stack of methodTree I'm entering, and just checking the top of the stack is NOT the loadUserByUsername method.
For the other parent loop, I can see it will anyway stop fast. For this one, it will stop too early, and making it more general will trigger the loop until the parent is null which we want to avoid.

