Firstly, I refactored it to additional method visitor. So it checked each method which wasn't loadUserByUsername and reported an issue each time an exception UserNotFoundException was found.
Then I realized that this way we're going to check all methods in class. And a chance to meet this exception is quite low. I suppose It's better to check exact throw statement if it is in scope of the loadUserByUsername method. The only solution that came to my mind will be :
private static boolean isInsideLoadUserByUserName(Tree tree) {
    Tree current = tree.parent();
    while (current != null) {
        if (current.is(Tree.Kind.METHOD) && LOAD_USER_MATCHER.matches(((MethodTree) current))) {
            return true;
        }
        current = current.parent();
    }
    return false;
}

Is it ok or am I missing something?

