If a rule is stateful, it's mandatory to clean the state when entering the file and it's usually done by overriding:
  @Override
  public void setContext(JavaFileScannerContext context) {
    mystate.clear();
    super.setContext(context);
  }

Because you don't know if an exception previously occurs during the last analyzed file. When an exception occurs, leaveNode is not called, the sate is stale, and a recovery mechanism continues with the next file.
Finally, you can also keep the cleanup in the leaveNode method, it frees the memory before the next file.
